parameters:
May 18, 1976: From tomorrow, I will undertake the
ascetic practices of Shugendo. It's a grueling
ten-day training, but it's an important task to
cultivate the spiritual power needed to calm the
spirits that torment the living beings.

I must continue to work hard and catch up to my
master.

June 2, 1976: I feel a slight increase in my
spiritual power. It seems that the daily
purification and meditation are having an effect.
Tomorrow, I will face my first exorcism. I want to
prove that I can save people.

February 3, 1979: The master has disappeared. He
went out to exorcise a major curse he had planned
to confront for some time and hasn't returned for
two months.

Could it be that the master was defeated? And I
have yet to repay him for saving me.

August 7, 1981: Today is an extremely hot day. I
managed to make contact with an elderly psychic
who knows clues about the master, but I was told
that I'm not strong enough to challenge the
mansion.

Even his disciple, who was called a genius,
challenged the mansion and never returned. In
those circles, it's known as the "Cursed Moon
Mansion," a name that is shunned even in speech.

September 20, 1983: I found a shrine in the
mountains. The decayed shrine is filled with a
hideous curse. Perhaps its deity was also consumed
by the "Cursed Moon Mansion."

Can I really overcome a curse that even swallows
gods?

January 9, 1987: At last, I will challenge the
mansion. I've found a path that leads to it from
within the city. Now, having honed my spiritual
power to surpass my master's and become a psychic
known to all in the area, it's time.

The time has come for me to avenge my master and
release the long-standing curse.

January 10, 1987: I don't want to die I don't want
to die I don't want to die I don't want to die I
don't want to die I don't want to die I don't want
to die I don't want to die I don't want to die I
don't want to die I don't want to die I don't want
to die

I don't want to die if I die I'll be consumed
souls will be swallowed it's terrifying it's
terrifying the cursed moon is not something humans
can handle I too will be taken cursed by the land
There's nothing written beyond this point.
